text.section:
The application shall:
Be sworn to;
State the name of the applicant and each of the applicant's affiliates and operating subsidiaries engaged in business as a mortgage loan company or a mortgage loan broker;
State the name under which the applicant will conduct business in Kentucky;
State the physical address of the applicant's principal office and branch or branches;
List the name, residence, and business address of each person having an interest in the business as principal, partner, officer, trustee, and director, specifying the capacity and title of each;
Indicate the general plan and character of the business;
Contain a corporate surety bond or other instrument as prescribed by KRS 286.8-060;
If applying for a mortgage loan broker license, contain a compiled financial statement of the applicant; or, if applying for a mortgage loan company license, contain a reviewed or audited financial statement of the applicant prepared by a licensed or certified public accountant;
Include payment of the required fees; and
Include such other information as the commissioner determines necessary.
